# IIR biquad-ish: y[n] = a*y[n-1] + b*x[n].
*iir(x as Vec of i64, n as i64, a as i64, b as i64) returns i64
    y is 0
    i is 0
    while i < n
        y is (a * y + b * x.get(i)) / 100
        i is i + 1
    y

*main
    x is vec()
    i is 0
    while i < 50
        x.push(100 + (i * 7 % 11))
        i is i + 1
    log iir(x, 50, 80, 20)
